<p><br></p>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"ChurnPredictionProject-Step4:FeatureImportance"><strong>Step 4: F=
eature Importance</strong></h2>
<h3 id=3D"ChurnPredictionProject-RandomForest-ManualTuning:">RandomForest -=
 Manual Tuning:</h3>
<ul>
 <li>
  <p><strong><code>last_interval</code> (13.5):</strong> The most important=
 feature. The time gap between the 3rd and 4th purchase is the strongest si=
gnal for predicting the 5th purchase. <strong>Longer gaps increase the like=
lihood of churn.</strong></p></li>
 <li>
  <p><strong><code>total_duration</code> (12.5):</strong> Indicates the ove=
rall pace of completing the first 4 purchases. Users who follow a consisten=
t and faster rhythm tend to be <strong>more loyal</strong>.</p></li>
 <li>
  <p><strong><code>avg_interval</code> (10.7):</strong> The average time be=
tween purchases. Helps the model assess whether a user=E2=80=99s behavior i=
s <strong>=E2=80=9Cnormal=E2=80=9D or consistent</strong>.</p></li>
 <li>
  <p><strong><code>carton_count_std</code> (10.6) &amp;&nbsp;<code>line_of_=
factor_std</code> (10.0):</strong> Both relate to behavioral stability. Hig=
h variability in carton counts or item diversity per order signals <strong>=
unpredictable behavior</strong>, which in this dataset correlates with <str=
ong>higher churn probability</strong>.</p></li>
</ul>
<p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper confluence-embedded-manu=
al-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image" draggable=3D"false" width=
