<hr>
<h2 id=3D"ChurnPredictionProject-Step6:ActionableInsights"><strong>Step 6: =
Actionable Insights</strong></h2>
<p><strong>1.Early Warning System</strong><br>
  Since <em>last_interval</em> is the most critical factor, it=E2=80=99s re=
commended that the product team implement a system where, if the time since=
 a user=E2=80=99s last purchase exceeds their <strong>personal avg_interval=
</strong> (e.g., 1.5=C3=97), an <strong>automated SMS reminder</strong> or =
<strong>personalized offer</strong> is sent. This helps prevent the user fr=
om =E2=80=9Ccooling off.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p><strong>2.Consistency Campaign</strong><br>
  Given the importance of <strong>standard deviation features</strong>, use=
rs with highly variable baskets are at higher risk of churn. The operations=
 team can provide <strong>stable, subscription-like offers</strong> to guid=
e these users=E2=80=99 purchasing behavior toward consistency.</p>
<p><strong>3.Growth Recovery Plan</strong></p>
<p>We saw that a negative growth rate (when the basket size in the fourth p=
urchase is smaller than in the first purchase) is one of the signs of churn=
. For users whose<strong> fourth purchase value has decreased</strong> comp=
ared to the average of their first three purchases, run a <strong>targeted =
upsell campaign</strong>.&nbsp;Instead of giving a general discount, offer =
discounts on the categories the user used to buy before but are now missing=
 from their basket. This can help bring the =E2=80=9Cbasket depth=E2=80=9D =
back to its normal level.</p>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"ChurnPredictionProject-Step7:SuggestedAdditionalDataandFeatures">=
<strong>Step 7: Suggested Additional Data and Features</strong></h2>
<p>According to the task, if more data were available, the following featur=
es could further improve model accuracy:</p>
<ul>
 <li>
  <p><strong>Behavioral Data (App Event Logs):</strong> Number of times the=
 user opens the app or searches for products without completing a purchase.=
 This provides insight into <strong>purchase intent</strong> before a trans=
action occurs.</p></li>
 <li>
  <p><strong>Category Breadth:</strong> The number of <strong>different pro=
duct categories</strong> a user purchases from (e.g., dairy, protein, etc.)=
. Greater diversity typically increases <strong>platform stickiness</strong=
>.</p></li>
 <li>
  <p><strong>Support Interaction (Support Tickets):</strong> Whether the us=
er submitted complaints or support requests after the 3rd or 4th purchase. =
Poor early experiences are a major driver of churn.</p></li>
 <li><strong>Logistics Data: </strong>The time gap between =E2=80=9Corder p=
lacement=E2=80=9D and =E2=80=9Cproduct delivery,=E2=80=9D and the delivery =
delay rate + Adding <strong>Delivery Delay</strong> as a feature can greatl=
y improve the prediction power of the model.</li>
 <li><strong>Payment Method:</strong> Does the user pay in cash, or do they=
 use credit (Credit/Wallet)?</li>
</ul>
<p><br></p>
<p><br></p>
